  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "Truffle has a dependency on `ipfs-http-client` which has a transitive dependency `ursa-optional` that causes a node-gyp process bomb when bootstrapping truffle with NodeJS > v15 along with npm > 6.x.  This bomb will eventually consume all system memory. \r\n\r\nIf you find yourself in this situation\r\n - kill all node processes using `pkill node`, you may have to run it several times to make sure you get them all.\r\n - install npm@6 `npm install -g npm@6`\r\n\r\nThe root cause of this issue is the transitive dependency `ursa-optional`'s scripts.  Unfortunately, [ipfs-http-client](https://github.com/ipfs/js-ipfs/blob/master/packages/ipfs-http-client/CHANGELOG.md#-breaking-changes) has a fix, which drops the dependency, but requires NodeJS > 15. \r\n\r\n",
